Vice President Kamala Harris and Prime Minister Philip Davis of The Commonwealth of The Bahamas will host the U.S-Caribbean Leaders Meeting in Nassau, The Bahamas on June 8, 2023. The meeting aims to strengthen cooperation between the United States and the Caribbean. The Vice President has previously met with Caribbean leaders in April 2022, June 2022, and September 2022. The Vice President's trip will address various issues including security and firearms trafficking, the need for an enhanced diplomatic presence in the eastern Caribbean, the crisis in Haiti, and the U.S.â€“Caribbean Partnership to Address the Climate Crisis 2030 (PACC 2030). Over $100 million in new assistance for the region will be announced, focusing on initiatives to improve security, increase diplomatic presence, address the crisis in Haiti, and advance climate adaptation and clean energy access. Progress has been made in improving access to development financing, facilitating clean energy project development and investment, and enhancing local capacity building.